The paper deals with the analysis of structured random embeddings, which is a topic that falls under the purview of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of decoupling techniques and matrix-valued Bernstein inequalities suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the Laplace transform technique used in the paper is a common tool in signal processing (cs.SI).
